2	The Filth	The Filth was designed to showcase new Artists and talent. Our intention is that you will sample our tunes to find new music. 	--- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSS \ndescription: Music Blog, Event, & Lifestyle\nentries: \n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: connor\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - cassette culture\n  - delta heavy\n  - Drum and Bass\n  - jungle friction\n  - moombah tone\n  - Moombahton\n  - nerp\n  - Shock One\n  - tantrum desire\n  - utah saints\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/5094418834_7f0f872d1c.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-3912" title="5094418834_7f0f872d1c" src="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/5094418834_7f0f872d1c-300x298.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="298" /></a></p>\n    <p>Hello again by Filthy followers. Looking for something crunchy to get you through the rest of the week? Well look no further. I&#8217;ve picked out a few of my old favorites, and newly found gems for you to bang your head to. It&#8217;s that time of the year when life is going to get you stressed no matter who you are. Be sure to keep your ears to The Filth to get those juicy bass bangers to calm your soul.</p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/q503n9g8w7aujsk/WCYDFM (Tantrum Desire Remix).mp3">Utah Saints &#8211; What Can You Do For Me (Tantrum Desire Remix)</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/ip9j8gdly4wdim8/We Once Had An Empire (Jungle Fiction Remix).mp3">Cassette Culture &#8211; We Once Had An Empire (Jungle Friction Remix)</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/cdd9chx02u798r2/Crush On You (Knife Party VIP Mix) (Transcoded).mp3">Nero &#8211; Crush On You (Knife Party VIP Remix)</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/elhpt8pwc694e1f/03 Polygon (Shock One VIP).mp3">Shock One &#8211; Polygon (Shock One VIP Remix)</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/l6b7wnbnrulcrzm/Overkill.mp3">Delta Heavy &#8211; Overkill</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/xdazg2g3m972hn2/Must Be The Feeling by Nero (Delta Heavy Remix).mp3">Nero &#8211; Must Be The Feeling (Delta Heavy Remix)</a></p>\n    <p>Filthier than thou.</p>\n    <p>-Connoisseur</p>\n\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3910\n  published: 2012-02-08 04:36:36 Z\n  summary: Hello again by Filthy followers. Looking for something crunchy to get you through the rest of the week? Well look no further. I&#8217;ve picked out a few of my old &#8230;<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://thefilth.us/2012/02/08/nero-delta-heavy-knife-party-tantrum-desire-and-more/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#187;</span></a>\n  title: Nero, Delta Heavy, Knife Party, Tantrum Desire and More!\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2012/02/08/nero-delta-heavy-knife-party-tantrum-desire-and-more/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: connor\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - rage face records\n  - the robot dentist\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/robotdentistbanner.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3906\\" title=\\"robotdentistbanner\\" src=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/robotdentistbanner-300x121.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"300\\" height=\\"121\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>The day has arrived! The long awaited EP from <a href=\\"http://www.ragefacerecords.com/artists/robot-dentist/\\">The Robot Dentist</a> is finally here. Coming out of the Windy City, The Robot Dentist has a teeth-shattering sound that I have yet to encounter. Born Ian Squires, he has assumed his super-alter-ego The Robot Dentist. As the fore-runner on<a href=\\"http://www.ragefacerecords.com/\\"> Rage Face Records</a> he has been mixing together a beautifully eclectic style infusing Trance, Electro, Dubstep and sounds that have yet to have a genera. There&#8217;s not much I\\xC2\\xA0can say that his music can&#8217;t.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/5d54blk0v141k8k/02 I Feel So Bad (Original Mix).mp3\\">The Robot Dentist &#8211; I Feel So Bad</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/72371vx81ciqai2/03 Keep Bouncing (Original Mix).mp3\\">The Robot Dentist &#8211; Keep Bouncing</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/wj7ckc7gq2my4iz/01 Trick Digital (Original Mix).mp3\\">The Robot Dentist &#8211; Trick Digital</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/co271g22gq18gtq/04 Trick Digital (Enoptix Remix).mp3\\">The Robot Dentist &#8211; Trick Digital (Enoptix Remix)</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>I&#8217;ve never felt better about going to the Dentist.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Filthier than thou.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>-Connoisseur</p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3905\n  published: 2012-01-24 01:16:03 Z\n  summary: The day has arrived! The long awaited EP from The Robot Dentist is finally here. Coming out of the Windy City, The Robot Dentist has a teeth-shattering sound that I &#8230;<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://thefilth.us/2012/01/23/new-bass-cavity-ep/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#187;</span></a>\n  title: New Bass Cavity EP!\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2012/01/23/new-bass-cavity-ep/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: connor\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - BASS\n  - Dr. Dre\n  - drum\n  - Drum and Bass\n  - drumstep\n  - figure\n  - knife party\n  - mitis\n  - poisound\n  - the killabits\n  - Zed's Dead\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/artworks-000014165269-4nmlxz-crop.jpeg\\"><img class=\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3899\\" title=\\"artworks-000014165269-4nmlxz-crop\\" src=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/artworks-000014165269-4nmlxz-crop-300x300.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"300\\" height=\\"300\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Aloha Filthy Friends! My\\xC2\\xA0apologies\\xC2\\xA0for having such a large gap between posts. But I&#8217;m back and filthier than ever. I have some out of this WORLD tracks for you today. Dirty bass and Drum &amp; Bass is the name of the game today.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>First up my absolute favorite track at the moment. Keep your eyes on Mitis.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/zvnetgf53gx7j8f/01 Give My Regards (Original Mix).mp3\\">Mitis &#8211; Give My Regards</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Next an Incredible Drumstep remix of Internet Friends.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/0ykqbjrm44zd7ne/Internet friends (Poisound remix refix).mp3\\">Knife Party &#8211; Internet Friends (Poisound Remix)</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>If you ever have a chance to see figure like I did a few weeks ago I highly\\xC2\\xA0recommend\\xC2\\xA0it.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/5qup13o6q618co8/Keep Their Heads Ringin (Figure Drumstep Bootleg).mp3\\">Dr. Dre &#8211; Heads Ringin&#8217; (Figure Drumstep Remix)</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/m9uzd3w6tmbanjc/02 Bassmentality (Figure Drumstep Remix) (Original Mix).mp3\\">Zeds Dead &amp; The Killabits (Figure Drumstep Remix)</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Filthier than thou.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>-Connoisseur</p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3897\n  published: 2012-01-19 03:43:19 Z\n  summary: "Aloha Filthy Friends! My\\xC2\\xA0apologies\\xC2\\xA0for having such a large gap between posts. But I&#8217;m back and filthier than ever. I have some out of this WORLD tracks for you today. Dirty &#8230;<a class=\\"continue_reading_link\\" href=\\"http://thefilth.us/2012/01/18/wobble-wednesday/\\">Continue reading <span class=\\"meta-nav\\">&#187;</span></a>"\n  title: Wobble Wednesday\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2012/01/18/wobble-wednesday/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: brittany\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/hardsf-227.jpg\\"><br />\\n\\\n    <img class=\\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3870\\" title=\\"hardsf-227\\" src=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/hardsf-227-188x300.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"188\\" height=\\"300\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Friday January 13<sup>th</sup> HARD, RedEye and Mezzanine present San Francisco with the Bromance Tour featuring Brodinski, Gesaffelstein, and Destructo. T&#8217;was love at first sight when the two French producers, Brodinski and Gesaffelstein, joined hand in hand to create, collab, and tour the world as Bromance. Brodinski has been a household name since 2007, while Gesaffelstein has emerged as one of our favorite techno heavy weights of 2011. 2011 was a golden year for the two. Brodinski teamed up with Gesafelstein to form Bromance Records and release their first EP, Bromance #1. Many of us who have heard Brodinski&#8217;s essential mix may be skeptical of his productions, but his song<em> Let the Beat Control Your Body </em>(Bromance #1 EP)\\xC2\\xA0has lived up to its name. Gesaffelstein&#8217;s set at HARD summer in LA was pure techno bliss and his song <em>Control Movement </em>(Bromance #1 EP) is incredible. I can&#8217;t wait to hear these two on Mezzanine&#8217;s Funktion Ones! See you there.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Our good friends at RedEye Presents have graced us with two tickets to giveaway to our lovely followers.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/TheFilth.us\\">CLICK HERE FOR TICKET GIVEAWAY</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">FRIDAY January 13th, 2011</span></span></span><br />\\n\\\n    <span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">Mezzanine</span></span></span><br />\\n\\\n    <span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">444 Jessie St</span></span></span><br />\\n\\\n    <span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">San Francisco, CA</span></span></span><br />\\n\\\n    <span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">21+ To Enter | Doors @ 9:30pm</span></span></span><br />\\n\\\n    <span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"> </span></span><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">PRESALE TICKETS ($20) &#8211;&gt; </span></span></span><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\"><a href=\\"http://mezzbromance.eventbrite.com/\\">http://mezzbromance.eventbrite.com/</a></span></span></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\"><a href=\\"http://mezzbromance.eventbrite.com/\\"></a></span></span></span><a href=\\"http://www.redeyelife.com/\\"><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">http://www.redeyelife.com/</span></span></span></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.facebook.com/redeyelife\\"><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">http://www.facebook.com/redeyelife</span></span></span></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.hard.com/\\"><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">www.hard.com</span></span></span></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.facebook.com/hardpresents\\"><span style=\\"color: #2d438b;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\">www.facebook.com/hardpresents</span></span></span></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Brodinski - Let the Beat Control Your Body\\" href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/mn8928idf8zkc7n/Brodinski - Let The Beat Control Your Body (daftwho.com).mp3\\">Brodinski &#8211; Let the Beat Control Your Body </a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Gesaffelstein - Control Movement\\" href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/w3bc5cvdeak8n8z/88-Gesaffelstein - Control Movement (Original Mix) .mp3\\">Gesaffelstein &#8211; Control Movement</a></p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3892\n  published: 2012-01-10 06:43:01 Z\n  summary: Friday January 13th HARD, RedEye and Mezzanine present San Francisco with the Bromance Tour featuring Brodinski, Gesaffelstein, and Destructo. T&#8217;was love at first sight when the two French producers, Brodinski &#8230;<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://thefilth.us/2012/01/10/bromance-sf/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#187;</span></a>\n  title: BROMANCE SF\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2012/01/10/bromance-sf/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: brittany\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - blasthaus\n  - Dance\n  - Digitalism\n  - filth\n  - mezzanine\n  - san francisco\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/digitalism-web-new.png\\"><img class=\\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-3871\\" title=\\"digitalism web new\\" src=\\"http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/12/digitalism-web-new-199x300.png\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"199\\" height=\\"300\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Dear fellow Filtheteers,</p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">I am a survivor of the Finals epidemic. Like many others, I was quarantined to the library where my brain endured injections of information that I will never remember. But now that finals are over, sleep deprivation will only be due to the ingestion of stimulants on the dance floor. With that said it is my pleasure to invite you to the live performance of Digitalism at Mezzanine, San Francisco.</span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/events/100927680022826/\\"> </a><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/events/100927680022826/\\">On Wednesday December 14<sup>th</sup>, Blasthaus and Mezzanine present Digitalism (LIVE) </a>with support from Anna Lunoe, Data Romance, and Eli Glad. Digitalism consists of Jens &#8220;Jence&#8221; Moelle and \\xC4\\xB0smail &#8220;Isi&#8221; T\\xC3\\xBCfek\\xC3\\xA7i from Hamburg, Germany. The duo is known for producing electro-rock dance music, which has earned them the rights to remix tracks for The Presets, Tom Vek,The Futureheads, Daft Punk, Tiga, Klaxons, White Stripes, Monk, Depeche Mode, Cut Copy and many others, including a re-edit of \\xE2\\x80\\x9CFire in Cairo\\xE2\\x80\\x9D by The Cure (entitled \\xE2\\x80\\x9CDigitalism in Cairo\\xE2\\x80\\x9D). I suggest you buy your ticket <a href=\\"http://digimezz.eventbrite.com/\\">HERE</a>, before it is sold out!</span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"> </span><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">We understand that money is tight during the holidays, so our friends at Blasthaus have provided us with four tickets to giveaway to our Filthy followers. </span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/TheFilth.us\\">\\xE2\\x86\\x92 <span style=\\"font-family: LucidaGrande;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: x-small;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\">GIVEAWAY HERE! \\xE2\\x86\\x90</span></span></span></span></a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #262626; font-size: small;\\">Event info:<br />\\n\\\n    Wednesday, December 14th 9pm-2am<br />\\n\\\n    Blasthaus &amp; Mezzanine present: Digitalism (LIVE), Data Romance, Anna Lunoe, and Eli Glad<br />\\n\\\n    Mezzanine / 444 Jessie St. / San Francisco<br />\\n\\\n    21+ / $20 Ltd Adv tickets<br />\\n\\\n    Tickets via Eventbrite: http://digimezz-mezzsite.eventbrite.com/<br />\\n\\\n    </span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #262626; font-size: small;\\">Tunes from Digitalism&#8217;s newest album <em>I Love You Dude</em></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/9v2for8n2tc3bo4/Digitalism%20-%20Stratosphere.mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; Stratosphere</a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/j8pzjlswobdzuex/Digitalism%20-%202%20Hearts.mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; 2 Hearts</a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/gnzmjoxjlnb/Digitalism%20-%20Echoes.mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; Echoes</a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\">And a few more goodies :) </span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/onyglzhnemu/Digitalism%20-%20Home%20Zone%20_Proxy%20Remix_.mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; Home Zone ( Proxy Remix)</a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/znz5ezxjywt/Digitalism%20-%20Apollo%20Gize%20(Breakbot%20Hypnotoad%20Extended%20Remix).mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; Apollo Gize (Breakbot Hypotoad Extended Remix) </a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small;\\"><a href=\\"http://www.mediafire.com/file/mint2d5zmm4/Idealistic%20(A-Trak%20Remix).mp3\\">Digitalism &#8211; Idealistic (A-Trak Remix) </a></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Enjoy,</p>\\n\\\n    <p>xo Shwitt</p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #000000;\\"><span style=\\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\\"><span style=\\"font-size: small;\\"> </span></span></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"><br />\\n\\\n    </span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"> </span><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"> </span><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"> </span><span style=\\"color: #262626;\\"> </span></p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3872\n  published: 2011-12-08 21:23:04 Z\n  summary: Dear fellow Filtheteers, I am a survivor of the Finals epidemic. Like many others, I was quarantined to the library where my brain endured injections of information that I will &#8230;<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://thefilth.us/2011/12/08/digitalism-live-mezzanine-sf/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#187;</span></a>\n  title: Digitalism (LIVE) @ Mezzanine SF\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2011/12/08/digitalism-live-mezzanine-sf/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: connor\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/SnowGlobe_Lineup_2011.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-3862" title="SnowGlobe_Lineup_2011" src="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/SnowGlobe_Lineup_2011-194x300.jpg" alt="" width="194" height="300" /></a></p>\n    <p>Aloha my filthy brethren, its Connoisseur explaining to you exactly what your doing on New Years Eve. That&#8217;s right, you have no choice but to attend <a href="http://snowglobemusicfestival.com/">Snowglobe Music Festiva</a>l in Tahoe. Wether by plane, hitchhiking, or magic carpet ride, you have no excuse to miss this incredible lineup. With headlining artists Bassnectar, Pretty Lights, Thievery Corporation, and The Glitch Mob, supported by other artists like Doctor P, Big Gigantic, Porter Robinson, Figure, Paper Diamond and Dillon Francis (to name a fraction), this is something only a fool would miss. You can purchase your tickets <a href="http://snowglobemusicfestival.com/tickets/general-admission/">HERE</a>. be sure to grab your tickets ASAP because they&#8217;re flying off the shelves!</p>\n    <p>Here&#8217;s a few tracks to get you started.</p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/b5a7ffg1j1l0eaq/Scroobius%20Pip%20-%20The%20Struggle%20(Doctor%20P%20Mix)%20(BacauHouseMafia.Ro).mp3">Scroobius Pip &#8211; The Struggle (Doctor P Mix)</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/njmz5k1s3wpltz4/01%20Spitfire%20(Original%20Mix).mp3">Porter Robinson &#8211; Spitfire</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.mediafire.com/file/48mng86mgkd21gj/Lassitude%20(Dillon%20Francis%20Remix).mp3">Dj Fresh &amp; Sigma &#8211; Lassitude (Dillon Francis Remix)</a></p>\n    <p>Filthier than thou.</p>\n    <p>-Connoisseur</p>\n\n  entry_id: http://thefilth.us/?p=3861\n  published: 2011-11-16 05:38:44 Z\n  summary: Aloha my filthy brethren, its Connoisseur explaining to you exactly what your doing on New Years Eve. That&#8217;s right, you have no choice but to attend Snowglobe Music Festival in &#8230;<a class="continue_reading_link" href="http://thefilth.us/2011/11/16/nye/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#187;</span></a>\n  title: NYE\n  url: http://thefilth.us/2011/11/16/nye/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: connor\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - aaa & Atom bass\n  - androa\n  - ark instint\n  - boy kid cloud\n  - caveat\n  - dada life\n  - figure\n  - heliopter showdown\n  - the misfits\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/figure-halloween.jpg"><img src="http://thefilth.us/blog/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/figure-halloween.jpg" alt="" title="figure-halloween" width="640" height="640" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-3855" /></a></p>\n    <p>Boo! Did I get ya&#8217;? Probably not, but these sickening tracks most definitely will. I think Figure has taken it upon himself to produce my entire Halloween playlist. Remixing a classic Misfits track as well as