ame width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"166\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F36368942&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe><br />\\n\\\n    <iframe width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"166\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F35924022&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe><br />\\n\\\n    <iframe width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"166\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F36763370&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe><br />\\n\\\n    <iframe width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"166\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F36525997&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe><br />\\n\\\n    <iframe width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"166\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F36424817&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe><br />\\n\\\n    <iframe width=\\"100%\\" height=\\"450\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"no\\" src=\\"http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Fplaylists%2F1493249&#038;show_artwork=true\\"></iframe></p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13422\n  published: 2012-02-17 15:52:50 Z\n  summary: "How do you prefer your remixes? Soundcloud or just a link? Leonard Friend &#8211; Everything for the Sake of Everything (Luke Top Remix) Yusek-Off the Wall (Brodinski Remix) R\\xC3\\xB6yksopp &#8220;R\\xC3\\xB6yksopp Forever&#8221; (Pardon My Friends Mashup Mix) CARTER TANTON-In Knots (+ Distal Remix)"\n  title: Friday Remixes\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/friday-remixes-117/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Concerts\n  - concert review\n  - cover\n  - fox theatre\n  - la guns\n  - nurses\n  - portland\n  - stephen malkmus & the jicks\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886797251/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7190/6886797251_a0270fd0f7_z.jpg" width="612" height="612" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p>Portland invaded Boulder for one evening with Stephen Malkmus &#038; the Jicks with Nurses brought some Rose love to the land of patchouli. <span id="more-13410"></span> I say that because the guy next to me wreaked of it, nearly passing out in the process. Nurses held their own with the heavy reverb and falsetto vocals that managed to overcome the less than stellar sound at the Fox Theatre. The material relied heavily on the mind warping release of &#8220;Dracula&#8221; that hit it&#8217;s high pitch with &#8220;Fever Dream.&#8221; I still have that beat stuck in my head and my feet won&#8217;t stop tapping along. </p>\n    <p>It&#8217;s safe to say that I&#8217;ve caught almost every Malkmus performance withing a 700 mile radius. I don&#8217;t remember the Jicks relying so heavily on the extended jams. I started having flashbacks of Trey, Paige, Mike and Jon going on an extended twenty minute &#8220;Tweezer&#8221; teaser when the show ended last night with &#8220;1% of One.&#8221; Not as much stage banter as recent shows, however, the new drummer, Jake Morris (the Joggers) did a serviceable job filling in for the departed and very talented Janet Weiss who is drumming with Wild Flag. &#8220;Brain Gallop&#8221; blindsided me with how much fun the four were having on stage and it showed with the improvisation from multi-instrumentalist, Mike Clark. It was nice to hear classics like &#8220;Church on White&#8221; and the very apropos, &#8220;Jenny and the Ess Dog,&#8221; you know, being in Boulder and all. On the way out, it dawned on me that the Jicks have been together longer than Pavement. Crazy. In case you ever wanted to hear the Jicks cover La Guns, now&#8217;s your chance. Head over <a href="http://www.makinwhoopee.ca/2012/02/mitchmatic-its-probably-raining-why.html">here</a> and listen at the 1:48:10. Let&#8217;s hope that they don&#8217;t stop with one 80&#8242;s glam metal band cover. </p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.matadorrecords.com/mpeg/stephen_malkmus_jicks/tigers.mp3">Stephen Malkmus &#038; the Jicks-Tigers [mp3]</a><br />\n    <a href="http://www.scjag.com/mp3/do/tryingtoreachyou.mp3">Nurses-Trying to Reach You [mp3]</a><br />\n    <a href="http://www.scjag.com/mp3/do/feverdreams.mp3">Nurses-Fever Dreams [mp3]</a></p>\n    <h2>Stephen Malkmus &#038; the Jicks</h2>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886772139/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7066/6886772139_42fa61bc83_z.jpg" width="612" height="408" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886779837/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7209/6886779837_aae443ed04_b.jpg" width="612" height="917" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886785419/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7038/6886785419_d5119b74df_b.jpg" width="612" height="408" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886793739/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7206/6886793739_8f0e0cc81a_b.jpg" width="612" height="917" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <h2>Nurses</h2>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886752275/" title="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7070/6886752275_b884a30fee_b.jpg" width="612" height="917" alt="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886753147/" title="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7186/6886753147_fa0bee39bd_b.jpg" width="612" height="612" alt="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886752641/" title="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7210/6886752641_338a8c9c15_b.jpg" width="612" height="612" alt="Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6886765123/" title="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7210/6886765123_d3a41a2100_b.jpg" width="612" height="408" alt="Stephen Malkmus &amp; the Jicks ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"></a></p>\n\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13410\n  published: 2012-02-16 18:45:23 Z\n  summary: Portland invaded Boulder for one evening with Stephen Malkmus &#038; the Jicks with Nurses brought some Rose love to the land of patchouli. I say that because the guy next to me wreaked of it, nearly passing out in the process. Nurses held their own with the heavy reverb and falsetto vocals that managed to [...]\n  title: "Stephen Malkmus & the Jicks // Nurses ::: Fox Theatre ::: 02.15.12"\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/stephen-malkmus-the-jicks-nurses-fox-theatre-02-15-12/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Videos\n  - miracle fortress\n  - pantha du prince\n  - Remix\n  - video\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://causeequalstime.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/was-i-the-wave.jpg"><img src="http://causeequalstime.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/was-i-the-wave.jpg" alt="" title="miracle fortress" width="612" height="612" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11392" /></a></p>\n    <p>Let me just put this out there right now: NOBODY was hurt during the filming of the &#8220;Raw Spectacle&#8221; video from <a href="http://www.causeequalstime.com/tag/miralce-fortress/">Miracle Fortress</a>.<span id="more-13403"></span> What I wouldn&#8217;t give to hear Beavis and Butthead commentate on this video. FIRE! FIRE! FIRE!</p>\n    <p><a href="http://causeequalstime.com/musique/Raw%20Spectacle%20(Pantha%20du%20Prince%20Remix).mp3">Miracle Fortress: Raw Spectacle (Pantha du Prince Remix)  [mp3]</a></p>\n    <p><iframe width="612" height="341" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/LRU5weqozoA" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13403\n  published: 2012-02-15 21:22:12 Z\n  summary: "Let me just put this out there right now: NOBODY was hurt during the filming of the &#8220;Raw Spectacle&#8221; video from Miracle Fortress. What I wouldn&#8217;t give to hear Beavis and Butthead commentate on this video. FIRE! FIRE! FIRE! Miracle Fortress: Raw Spectacle (Pantha du Prince Remix) [mp3]"\n  title: "Miracle Fortress \\xE2\\x80\\x9CRaw Spectacle\\xE2\\x80\\x9D video"\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/miracle-fortress-raw-spectacle-video/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - new album\n  - the mars volta\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://causeequalstime.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/IMG_12611.jpg"><img src="http://causeequalstime.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/IMG_12611-1024x682.jpg" alt="" title="IMG_1261" width="612" height="408" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-11253" /></a></p>\n    <p>We finally got our first taste off of the forthcoming Mars Volta album, &#8220;Noctourniquet&#8221; to be released March 27.<span id="more-13393"></span> &#8220;The Malkin Jewel&#8221; has a normal song title and very uncharacteristically un-Mars Volta like. Not to mention the vocals aren&#8217;t the normal Cedric nasally take, but a huskier version. The first single dabbles in the King Crimson territory and very curious to see how the rest of the album takes shape. Catch Omar and Cedric in Coachella for those At-the Drive in reunion shows.</p>\n    <p><iframe width="100%" height="450" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="http://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Fusers%2F4149032&#038;show_artwork=true"></iframe></p>\n\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13393\n  published: 2012-02-15 17:37:36 Z\n  summary: We finally got our first taste off of the forthcoming Mars Volta album, &#8220;Noctourniquet&#8221; to be released March 27. &#8220;The Malkin Jewel&#8221; has a normal song title and very uncharacteristically un-Mars Volta like. Not to mention the vocals aren&#8217;t the normal Cedric nasally take, but a huskier version. The first single dabbles in the King [...]\n  title: Listen to New Mars Volta\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/listen-to-new-mars-volta/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Concerts\n  - concert\n  - craig finn\n  - larimer lounge\n  - the hold steady\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877173941/" title="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7198/6877173941_06f8ec5ae3_b.jpg" width="612" height="612" alt="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12"></a></p>\n    <p>It&#8217;s important to point out that me seeing Craig Finn was very last minute.<span id="more-13396"></span> I heard an interview the other day where Finn was discussing the roots of the title of his new album, &#8220;Clear Heart Full Eyes.&#8221; The new album title is a nod to the TV show, &#8220;Friday Night Lights,&#8221; which possibly ties in as a coincidence that he recorded the release down in Austin. The Texas ties are running deep and the sound of the pedal steel last night spun the typical bar sound that Finn usually evokes with his day job, the Hold Steady. His normal Ginsberg fashion of talking versus singing found a happy medium last night when the story would segway into the song and towards the bridge, he would start exercising his voice a little more. Not fully singing, but I&#8217;m ok with that. For those locals that have been to a sold out Larimer show, you would know that the first couple of songs are crowded in the stage area and typically clears out by the third or fourth song filling the bar area. Last night, the bar stayed empty and Finn captivated everybody with his anecdotes of Burt Reynolds and Dom Deluise movies or leaving the big city with your tale between your legs. The solo effort has plenty of &#8220;Jesus&#8221; references, and the visit down to Texas could&#8217;ve served as a cathartic experience. I never liked the Hold Steady, but it might be time to visit &#8220;Separation Sunday.&#8221;</p>\n    <p><a href="http://causeequalstime.com/musique/05%20Jackson.mp3">Craig Finn-Jackson [mp3]</a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877171457/" title="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7043/6877171457_b24cc119ac_b.jpg" width="612" height="408" alt="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877168999/" title="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7200/6877168999_7801036c85_b.jpg" width="612" height="408" alt="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12"></a></p>\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877173647/" title="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7200/6877173647_bc7c6356f9_b.jpg" width="612" height="917" alt="Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12"></a></p>\n\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13396\n  published: 2012-02-14 22:02:20 Z\n  summary: It&#8217;s important to point out that me seeing Craig Finn was very last minute. I heard an interview the other day where Finn was discussing the roots of the title of his new album, &#8220;Clear Heart Full Eyes.&#8221; The new album title is a nod to the TV show, &#8220;Friday Night Lights,&#8221; which possibly ties [...]\n  title: "Craig Finn ::: Larimer Lounge ::: 02.13.12"\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/craig-finn-larimer-lounge-02-13-12/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Concerts\n  - ava luna\n  - concert review\n  - Hi-Dive\n  - young pharaohs\n  content: "<p><a title=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr\\" href=\\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877113169/\\"><img src=\\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7188/6877113169_951b96e163_b.jpg\\" alt=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12\\" width=\\"612\\" height=\\"612\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Ava Luna brought their brand of spazz soul last night to the Hi-Dive to show us how a sextet should look on stage. <span id=\\"more-13389\\"></span> The female vocals in charge of harmonies/backup consumed any attention that I had set aside for the rest of the act. Manic beats gave way to an established presence by a fairly young act that took anything the Dirty Projectors had ever done and took it to the next frontier. Their new album, &#8220;Ice Level,&#8221; will see the light of day February 28. </p>\\n\\\n    <p>From the ashes of King Mob comes Young Pharaohs. The trio are performing mostly new material with some King Mob jams for good measure. The limited material didn&#8217;t stunt the trio&#8217;s performance by leaning a  little more on their glitchy synth intuitions and less on the R&#038;B persuasion. The vocals by elder brother Martin seem more relaxed as the young act gains more experience. </p>\\n\\\n    <p><a id=\\"yui_3_3_0_1_13292505841271268\\" href=\\"../musique/04%20Wrenning%20Day.mp3\\">Ava Luna \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Wrenning Day [mp3]</a><br />\\n\\\n    <em title=\\"Play Audio\\"></em><a id=\\"yui_3_3_0_1_13292505841271278\\" href=\\"../musique/Mr.%20100.mp3\\">Young Pharaohs \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Mr 100 [mp3]</a></p>\\n\\\n    <h2>Ava Luna</h2>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr\\" href=\\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877115785/\\"><img src=\\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7193/6877115785_59bf026b94_b.jpg\\" alt=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12\\" width=\\"612\\" height=\\"408\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr\\" href=\\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877118579/\\"><img src=\\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7054/6877118579_3f15b63981_b.jpg\\" alt=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12\\" width=\\"612\\" height=\\"408\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr\\" href=\\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877121109/\\"><img src=\\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7063/6877121109_5edef8b585_b.jpg\\" alt=\\"Ava Luna ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12\\" width=\\"612\\" height=\\"408\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <h2>Young Pharaohs</h2>\\n\\\n    <p><a title=\\"Young Pharaohs ::: Hi-Dive ::: 02.13.12 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr\\" href=\\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/6877101943/\\"><img src=\\"http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7187/6877101943_a7a162ac79_b.jpg\\" alt=\\"Young Pharaohs ::