at after last night&#8217;s performance that she&#8217;s only half robotic when singing before a studio audience. There were signs of life and who knows, the public MIGHT actually see her tour get off the floor.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://thecivilwars.com\\">The Civil Wars</a> caught my attention last year when they appeared on World Cafe with David Dye and their story caught my attention about how their respective spouses cope with the cruel touring schedule that imposes it&#8217;s demanding will on musicians. The duo played a short one minute set on Sunday night&#8217;s Grammy&#8217;s and nailed it as much one could in one minute. </p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://causeequalstime.com/musique/Born%20to%20Die%20(Damon%20Albarn%20Remix).mp3\\">Lana Del Rey \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Born to Die (Damon Albarn Remix) [mp3]</a><br />\\n\\\n    <a href=\\"http://causeequalstime.com/musique/Barton_Hollow.mp3\\">The Civil Wars \\xE2\\x80\\x93 \\xE2\\x80\\x9CBarton Hollow\\xE2\\x80\\x9D [mp3]</a> </p>\\n\\\n    <h2>the Civil Wars &#8220;Birds of a Feather&#8221; on &#8216;Leno&#8217;</h2>\\n\\\n    <p><iframe id=\\"NBC Video Widget\\" width=\\"612\\" height=\\"403\\" src=\\"http://www.nbc.com/assets/video/widget/widget.html?vid=1385005\\" frameborder=\\"0\\"></iframe></p>\\n\\\n    <h2>Lana Del Rey &#8220;Video Games&#8221; live on &#8216;Kimmel&#8217;</h2>\\n\\\n    <p><iframe width=\\"612\\" height=\\"341\\" src=\\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/PPqhgm7R8c8\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\\n\\\n    <p><object width=\\"512\\" height=\\"360\\"><param name=\\"movie\\" value=\\"http://sgmc.streamguys.net/player/VideoPlayer.swf\\"></param><param name=\\"allowFullScreen\\" value=\\"true\\"></param><param name=\\"allowscriptaccess\\" value=\\"always\\"></param><param name=\\"wmode\\" value=\\"transparent\\"></param><param value=\\"configXML=http%3A//sgmc.streamguys.net/player/config2.cfm%3FAudioGUID%3D7e25f6a6-c6a0-43dc-9b8c-2623b57b5189%26CategoryGUID%3Dd41cf0d0-8996-48d1-b64e-c5dd456530e9\\" name=\\"flashvars\\"></param><embed src=\\"http://sgmc.streamguys.net/player/VideoPlayer.swf\\" type=\\"application/x-shockwave-flash\\" allowscriptaccess=\\"always\\" wmode=\\"transparent\\" allowfullscreen=\\"true\\" width=\\"512\\" height=\\"360\\" flashvars=\\"configXML=http%3A//sgmc.streamguys.net/player/config2.cfm%3FAudioGUID%3D7e25f6a6-c6a0-43dc-9b8c-2623b57b5189%26CategoryGUID%3Dd41cf0d0-8996-48d1-b64e-c5dd456530e9\\"></embed></object></p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://causeequalstime.com/?p=13384\n  published: 2012-02-14 15:32:49 Z\n  summary: The $hit storm that ensued after the Lana Del Rey performance was perfectly well put by SNL&#8217;s Kristen Wiig as Lana herself, stating &#8220;I must have clubbed a baby seal while singing the Taliban national anthem.&#8221; That about sums up the public sentiment about Lizzie Grant Lana Del Rey. Last night LDR checked to see [...]\n  title: "Kickin\\xE2\\x80\\x99 Television ::: the Civil Wars on Leno and Lana Del Rey on Kimmel"\n  url: http://causeequalstime.com/2012/02/kickin-television-the-civil-wars-on-leno-and-lana-del-rey-on-kimmel/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: julio\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - the Weekender\n  - chick in club\n  - dj richy\n  - Remix\n  - SNL\n  - the grammys\n  - the kills\n  - the weekender\n  - video\n  - whitney houston\n  - zooey deschanel\n  content: |\n    <p><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/julioenriquez/3219492431/" title="Adele :: Bluebird Theater :: 01.22.09 by Julio Enriquez, on Flickr"><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3317/3219492431_43a0a7c2af_b.jpg" width="612" height="917" alt="Adele :: Bluebird Theater :: 01.22.09"></a></p>\n    <p>Anything that was going or that was going to happen this weekend was eclipsed by the sudden passing of one of the original divas, Whitney Houston.<span id="more-13375"></span> Her bouts with drug dependency ended up winning in the end and everybody&#8217;s looking at Bobby Brown as the main culprit to her deterioration. I know, I know, it takes two to tango, but it&#8217;s still a damn shame. The Whitney tribute by the Grammy&#8217;s  was a classy number turned in by the svelte and extremely talented, Jennifer Hudson. <a href="http://www.grammy.com/">Here&#8217;s</a> a list of the winners from last night&#8217;s spectacle, but all you really had to know is that last tonight belonged to Adele. Her album, &#8220;21,&#8221; is a stunner from beginning to end and the release ended up winning some well deserved awards. I can safely say that after last night, I could probably do without seeing the Foo Fighters in any capacity and Foster the People turned in a snoozer cover of the Beach Boys. C&#8217;mon, guys. Show a little effort, you know, for the kids. </p>\n    <p>Rounding out the weekend is the tenth anniversary concert by the Kills and the intro by Zooey Deschanel on SNL. </p>\n    <p><a href="http://causeequalstime.com/musique/06%20-%20DNA.mp3">the Kills-DNA [mp3</a>]<br />\n    <a href="http://causeequalstime.com/musique/Adele%20-%20Rolling%20in%20the%20Deep%20(Chick%20In%20Club%20Remix).mp3">Adele-Rolling in the Deep (Chick in Club Remix)<br />\n    </a></p>\n    <div><object width="480" height="480"><param name="movie" value="http://www.mixcloud.com/media/swf/player/mixcloudLoader.swf?feed=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mixcloud.com%2Fdjrichy%2Fwhitney-houston-tribute-mini-mix%2F&#038;embed_uuid=7a1883d7-50af-4633-927c-ec1785ede380&#038;stylecolor=&#038;embed_type=widget_standard"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="wmode" value="opaque"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.mixcloud.com/media/swf/player/mixcloudLoader.swf?feed=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mixcloud.com%2Fdjrichy%2Fwhitney-houston-tribute-mini-mix%2F&#038;embed_uuid=7a1883d7-50af-4633-927c-ec1785ede380&#038;stylecolor=&#038;embed_type=widget_standard" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="opaque" allowscri