this, what\\xE2\\x80\\x99s better than a vulnerable, angst driven gangster rapper casually calling out a broad on a killer track?</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Well that\\xE2\\x80\\x99s easy, the above could be done by using Ryan Hemsworth&#8217;s Grimes-approved remix of &#8220;Genesis&#8221;.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Fortunately for us, that\\xE2\\x80\\x99s exactly what North Carolinian rapper Deniro Farrar did a few days back, and obviously the result is all kinds of trill.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><img class=\\"alignnone\\" title=\\"Grimes \\" src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/img/Grimes.jpg\\" alt=\\"Grimes \\" width=\\"500\\" height=\\"324\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p>I\\xE2\\x80\\x99m going to skip my spiritual seminar as to not offend any loyal followers, but I must say that this track is fate.\\xC2\\xA0 In case you haven\\xE2\\x80\\x99t heard, WinnieCooper.net and <a href=\\"http://www.timbreproductionsconcerts.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Timbre Concerts</a> present the beautiful yet darkly mysterious Grimes at Fortune Sound Club tonight! And just in case you didn\\xE2\\x80\\x99t think this could get anymore cray, Born Gold (formerly Gobble Gobble) will be accompanying Grimes to create an ethereal escape from reality. See you on the other side.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>While this event is sadly all sold out, I&#8217;ve included a few tracks below to help soften your heartbreak. xx.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/GrimesDeniro.mp3\\">Grimes Feat. Deniro Farrar &#8211; Genesis (Ryan Hemsworth Remix)\\xC2\\xA0</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/Oblivion.mp3\\">Grimes &#8211; Oblivion\\xC2\\xA0</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/AlabasterBodyworlds.mp3\\">Born Gold \\xC2\\xA0-\\xC2\\xA0Alabaster Bodyworlds</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>posted by <a href=\\"http://twitter.com/clarkbs\\">@clarkbs</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\\n\\n\\\n    \\t\\t\\t\\t<!-- Social Sharing Toolkit v2.0.4 | ht