Prescription drugs. Just as dangerous as &#8220;illegal&#8221; drugs.\\xC2\\xA0 Some silly mashups. rip Whitney. The Hood Internet &#8211; When The Night Knows (Whitney Houston x Chromeo) Zooash &#8211; Dancing in Houston (Robyn vs Whitney Houston) posted by @tristanorchard"\n  title: Whitney\n  url: http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/whitney/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Sam\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - Bad Girls\n  - M.I.A.\n  - Super Bowl XLVI\n  content: "<p><img class=\\"alignnone\\" title=\\"M.I.A.\\" src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/img/MIA.jpg\\" alt=\\"M.I.A. - Bad Girls \\" width=\\"458\\" height=\\"560\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p>I\\xE2\\x80\\x99d like to start off this post by thanking the always scandalous M.I.A.\\xC2\\xA0 During an extremely important interview last week my knowledge of her badass Superbowl antics garnered me much acclaim. You da best bb gurl.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Now on to more important things.\\xC2\\xA0 M.I.A. just dropped another bomb on the music industry. \\xC2\\xA0But instead of creating mass destruction, it\\xE2\\x80\\x99s about to foster a new generation of extremely stylish but hella rebellious young babes.\\xC2\\xA0 \\xE2\\x80\\x9CBad Girls\\xE2\\x80\\x9D was released late last month and it\\xE2\\x80\\x99s become the anthem for any girl wanting to live fast and die young.\\xC2\\xA0 It\\xE2\\x80\\x99s a throw back to her earlier work with \\xE2\\x80\\x9CArular\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and makes you wonder if she&#8217;s the raddest MILF out there.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>According to rumours, M.I.A. is currently in the studio working on her fourth full-length LP while simultaneously\\xC2\\xA0experiencing domestic difficulties with her billionaire baby daddy. And if history is any indicator, that is a solid concoction for great music.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><img class=\\"alignnone\\" title=\\"MIA - Bad Girls\\" src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/img/MIAWINNIE.jpg\\" alt=\\"MIA - Bad Girls \\" width=\\"472\\" height=\\"419\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/BadGirls.mp3\\">M.I.A. &#8211; Bad Girls\\xC2\\xA0</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Oh, and remember her music video for Born Free, or rather ginger genocide? Well she hooked up with the same director for \\xE2\\x80\\x9CBad Girls\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and although its sans controversy, you gotta check it out.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><iframe src=\\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/3Yuqxl284cg\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" width=\\"450\\" height=\\"259\\"></iframe></p>\\n\\\n    <p>posted by <a href=\\"http://twitter.com/clarkbs\\">@clarkbs</a></p>\\n\\n\\\n    \\t\\t\\t\\t<!-- Social Sharing Toolkit v2.0.4 | http://www.marijnrongen.com/wordpress-plugins/social_sharing_toolkit/ -->\\n\\\n    \\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\"mr_social_sharing_wrapper\\"><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><iframe src=\\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?locale=en_US&amp;href=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fm-i-a-bad-girls%2F&amp;layout=standard&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=51px&amp;height=24px\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" style=\\"border:none; overflow:hidden; width:51px; height:24px;\\" allowTransparency=\\"true\\"></iframe></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><div id=\\"fb-root\\"></div><fb:send href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/m-i-a-bad-girls/\\" font=\\"\\"></fb:send></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><a href=\\"http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fm-i-a-bad-girls%2F&amp;text=M.I.A.+%E2%80%93+Bad+Girls&amp;via=winnie_cooper\\" target=\\"_blank\\" class=\\"mr_social_sharing_popup_link\\"><img src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/wp-content/plugins/social-sharing-toolkit/images/buttons/twitter.png\\" alt=\\"Share on Twitter\\" title=\\"Share on Twitter\\"/></a></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><g:plusone size=\\"medium\\" href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/m-i-a-bad-girls/\\"></g:plusone></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><a href=\\"http://www.tumblr.com/share/link?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fm-i-a-bad-girls%2F&amp;name=M.I.A.+%E2%80%93+Bad+Girls\\" target=\\"_blank\\" class=\\"mr_social_sharing_popup_link\\"><img src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/wp-content/plugins/social-sharing-toolkit/images/buttons/tumblr.png\\" alt=\\"Share on Tumblr\\" title=\\"Share on Tumblr\\"/></a></span></div>"\n  entry_id: http://winniecooper.net/?p=16662\n  published: 2012-02-14 17:23:52 Z\n  summary: "I\\xE2\\x80\\x99d like to start off this post by thanking the always scandalous M.I.A.\\xC2\\xA0 During an extremely important interview last week my knowledge of her badass Superbowl antics garnered me much acclaim. You da best bb gurl. Now on to more important things.\\xC2\\xA0 M.I.A. just dropped another bomb on the music industry. \\xC2\\xA0But instead of creating [...]"\n  title: "M.I.A. \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Bad Girls"\n  url: http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/m-i-a-bad-girls/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Sam\n  categories: \n  - Music\n  - Electro\n  - Illangelo\n  - J Cole\n  - Mac Miller\n  - R&B\n  - Snoop Doog\n  - The Airplane Boys\n  - The Weeknd\n  content: "<p><img class=\\"alignnone\\" title=\\"The Airplane Boys\\" src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/img/theairplaneboys.jpg\\" alt=\\"The Airplane Boys\\" width=\\"478\\" height=\\"360\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p>I have a confession to make and I\\xE2\\x80\\x99m really not proud of it. \\xC2\\xA0I follow emo girls on Tumblr for the sole purpose of mocking their boy crazy binge rants.\\xC2\\xA0 Why am I telling you this? Well it seems that my despicable antics may have finally paid off.\\xC2\\xA0Let me explain.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Late this afternoon a YouTube video with the caption \\xE2\\x80\\x9CSuper Cute :)\\xE2\\x80\\x9D showed up on my newsfeed.\\xC2\\xA0 The video opened with two indie couples partaking in urban activities while a digitally inspired beat played in the background.\\xC2\\xA0 Just as I was about to close the window, a dude in a Levi\\xE2\\x80\\x99s denim jacket started spitting something futuristic.\\xC2\\xA0 To my surprise, this was actually the official music video for a track entitled \\xE2\\x80\\x9CGold Ribbons\\xE2\\x80\\x9D by <a href=\\"https://www.facebook.com/theairplaneboys?sk=wall\\" target=\\"_blank\\">the Airplane Boys</a>, a Canadian duo from T.O.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><iframe src=\\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/scfZwnbvKqo\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" width=\\"450\\" height=\\"259\\"></iframe></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Shortly after this humbling experience, I downloaded their mixtape \\xE2\\x80\\x9C<a href=\\"http://theairplaneboys.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Where\\xE2\\x80\\x99ve You Been</a>\\xE2\\x80\\x9D and quickly realized that I wasn\\xE2\\x80\\x99t the only one intrigued by this electro R&amp;B dream team.\\xC2\\xA0 The Airplane Boys, which consists of Beck Motley and Bon Voyag, have worked with Illangelo, one of the Weeknd\\xE2\\x80\\x99s producers, and toured with Mac Miller, J.Cole, Snoop Dogg, and the list goes on. With their first release you\\xE2\\x80\\x99ll see a sampling of the Arcade Fire and lyrics that rival Frank Ocean\\xE2\\x80\\x99s with their tortured quirkiness.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><img class=\\"alignnone\\" title=\\"The Airplane Boys\\" src=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/img/whereveyoubeen.jpg\\" alt=\\"The Airplane Boys\\" width=\\"466\\" height=\\"466\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/BornToBe.mp3\\">The Airplane Boys &#8211; Born to Be</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/Escape.mp3\\">The Airplane Boys &#8211; Escape\\xC2\\xA0</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/Weon.mp3\\">The Airplane Boys &#8211; Weon\\xC2\\xA0</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Their follow up mixtape &#8220;Alignment&#8221; is set to drop on February 16, with two singles (&#8220;New Blood&#8221; and &#8220;Dictate&#8221;) already available for download.\\xC2\\xA0 These tracks are sure to put you in a dopeness induced coma, as they somehow blend together electronic, urban, and indie pop, without sounding like T-Pain. Yet, what stand\\xE2\\x80\\x99s out the most is Motely and Voyag\\xE2\\x80\\x99s attention to lyrical detail. The cultural references are a plenty and they offer a social commentary that is both incredibly refreshing and disturbingly accurate.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>You definitely want to give these guys a listen because next year they\\xE2\\x80\\x99ll be all over the mainstream.</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/NewBlood.mp3\\">The Airplane Boys &#8211; New Blood</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/sam/2011/12/music/Dicate.mp3\\">The Airplane Boys &#8211; Dictate</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>posted by <a href=\\"http://twitter.com/clarkbs\\">@clarkbs</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\\n\\\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\\n\\\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\\n\\\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\\n\\n\\\n    \\t\\t\\t\\t<!-- Social Sharing Toolkit v2.0.4 | http://www.marijnrongen.com/wordpress-plugins/social_sharing_toolkit/ -->\\n\\\n    \\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\"mr_social_sharing_wrapper\\"><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><iframe src=\\"https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?locale=en_US&amp;href=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fthe-airplane-boys%2F&amp;layout=standard&amp;show_faces=false&amp;width=51px&amp;height=24px\\" scrolling=\\"no\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" style=\\"border:none; overflow:hidden; width:51px; height:24px;\\" allowTransparency=\\"true\\"></iframe></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><div id=\\"fb-root\\"></div><fb:send href=\\"http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/the-airplane-boys/\\" font=\\"\\"></fb:send></span><span class=\\"mr_social_sharing\\"><a href=\\"http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fthe-airplane-boys%2F&amp;text=The+Airplane+Boys&amp;via=winnie_cooper\\" target=\\"_blank\\" class=\\"mr_social_sharing_popup_link\\"><img src=