al mix</a> Friday night. In that essential mix, we heard a monster track created by Steve Angello, one of the members of Swedish House Mafia. I was also lucky to hear this track at SHM&#8217;s great performance at Madison Square Garden. &#8220;Yeah&#8221; is an Angello masterpiece and truly shows why he is considered one of the best DJs in the world. Check it out below.<br />\n    <iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/kEye1Kss9RY" frameborder="0" width="420" height="55"></iframe></p>\n\n  entry_id: http://yesgoodmusic.com/?p=9919\n  published: 2012-02-18 20:49:08 Z\n  summary: Swedish House Mafia has been on a tear recently. They officially titled their ID track &#8220;Greyhound&#8221; and they also took over Pete Tong&#8217;s essential mix Friday night. In that essential mix, we heard a monster track created by Steve Angello, one of the members of Swedish House Mafia. I was also lucky to hear this [...]\n  title: "Preview: Steve Angello \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Yeah"\n  url: http://yesgoodmusic.com/2012/02/18/preview-steve-angello-yeah/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Raffi\n  categories: \n  - -Home-\n  - Genres\n  - Hip-Hop\n  - Music Videos\n  - Rap\n  - Upcoming Artists/ Submissions\n  - lysick\n  - yolo\n  - you only live once\n  content: "<span style=\\"text-align:center; display: block;\\"><a href=\\"http://yesgoodmusic.com/2012/02/18/submission-yolo-you-only-live-once/\\"><img src=\\"http://img.youtube.com/vi/d6jm30MM9rA/2.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" /></a></span>\\n\\\n    <p>Although I don&#8217;t love that YOLO phrase, Lysick&#8217;s debut project, <em>YOLO </em>is definitely\\xC2\\xA0worth\\xC2\\xA0checking out. \\xC2\\xA0Watch the video for the title track from his <em>free album</em>\\xC2\\xA0above. The music video has over 230,000 views in less then a month, don&#8217;t sleep on the Montreal-based emcee Lysick. \\xC2\\xA0Reese Jones handles production on this joint and samples George Michael&#8217;s\\xC2\\xA0&#8221;Careless Whisper&#8221;\\xC2\\xA0for the collaboration between Lysick and\\xC2\\xA0Krystale. \\xC2\\xA0Read what Lysick had to say about his debut project below and listen/download the full album <a href=\\"http://yolo.bandcamp.com/album/yolo-you-only-love-once\\" target=\\"_blank\\">here</a>. \\xC2\\xA0Enjoy!</p>\\n\\\n    <blockquote><p>YOLO (You Only Love Once) marks Lysick\\xE2\\x80\\x98s debut into the rap game. While Drake and Rick Ross prepare their own version (You Only Live Once), Lysick took his own stance at the acronym. From the experience of others and his own, he quickly made a statement that fits the acronym, and realized that many only love once. Originally scheduled to be a mixtape, the free album draws inspiration from the lyricist\\xE2\\x80\\x98s past relationships or simply from the topic of love itself. Don\\xE2\\x80\\x99t let the title fool you, there is nothing cheesy about this body of work; Many will be surprised or shocked at the outcome and the twist the album takes. It is not an ordinary, common, or regular journey through love. What could it be? Only one way to find out. Lysick&#8217;s YOLO (You Only Love Once) is now out, Happy Valentine&#8217;s Day.</p></blockquote>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/Lysick/162385090493560?sk=app_204974879526524\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Like</a> Lysick on Facebook and <a href=\\"https://twitter.com/#!/Lysick_Wasiu\\" target=\\"_blank\\">Follow</a> Lysick on Twitter.</p>\\n"\n  entry_id: http://yesgoodmusic.com/?p=9920\n  published: 2012-02-18 20:30:50 Z\n  summary: "Although I don&#8217;t love that YOLO phrase, Lysick&#8217;s debut project, YOLO is definitely\\xC2\\xA0worth\\xC2\\xA0checking out. \\xC2\\xA0Watch the video for the title track from his free album\\xC2\\xA0above. The music video has over 230,000 views in less then a month, don&#8217;t sleep on the Montreal-based emcee Lysick. \\xC2\\xA0Reese Jones handles production on this joint and samples George Michael&#8217;s\\xC2\\xA0&#8221;Careless [...]"\n