rom it entitled &#8220;Clementine&#8221;. \\xC2\\xA0It picks up on the same subtle electronics that float through his previous work &#8211; really giving his folk croon some body behind it. \\xC2\\xA0It&#8217;s a track about family, aging, and passing of time and can also be heard during the documentary \\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://documentaries.org/cid-films/what-time-is-left/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/documentaries.org/cid-films/what-time-is-left/?referer=');\\">&#8220;What Time is Left&#8221;</a> by Dakin Henderson. \\xC2\\xA0Take a listen:</p>\\n\\\n    <p>mp3:\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://pastaprima.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/LouisWeeks_Clementine.mp3\\">Louis Weeks &#8211; Clementine</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Here&#8217;s another new one that is more along the lines of straight up Nick Drake-like folk:</p>\\n\\\n    <p>mp3:\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://pastaprima.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/LouisWeeks_GreatConversation.mp3\\">Louis Weeks &#8211; Great Conversation</a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Make sure you catch him this Thursday playing at the Ottobar here in Bmore with\\xC2\\xA0<strong>Swear and Shake</strong>.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>Louis Weeks Links:\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://www.louisweeksmusic.com/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.louisweeksmusic.com/?referer=');\\">Website</a>\\xC2\\xA0|\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://louisweeks.bandcamp.com/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/louisweeks.bandcamp.com/?referer=');\\">Bandcamp</a></p>\\n\\\n    <img src=\\"http://pastaprima.net/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=12744&type=feed\\" alt=\\"\\" />"\n  entry_id: http://pastaprima.net/?p=12744\n  published: 2012-02-14 14:11:23 Z\n  summary: "About a year ago I stumbled onto Baltimore&#8217;s\\xC2\\xA0Louis Weeks, a folkish singer-songwriter that strays into textural background studies. \\xC2\\xA0His song &#8220;Bloodline&#8221; was what initially sparked my interest. \\xC2\\xA0Now he&#8217;s working on a full LP and has sent over one from it entitled &#8220;Clementine&#8221;. \\xC2\\xA0It picks up on the same subtle electronics that float through his [...]"\n  title: "Louis Weeks \\xE2\\x80\\x93 Clementine (mp3)"\n  url: http://pastaprima.net/singles/louis-weeks-clementine-mp3/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: laurent the laurent\n  categories: \n  - Video\n  - HOV\n  content: "<p><img class=\\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-12739\\" title=\\"HOV\\" src=\\"http://pastaprima.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/Screen-shot-2012-02-12-at-8.52.03-PM-500x272.png\\" alt=\\"HOV\\" width=\\"500\\" height=\\"272\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p>HOV is the audio/visual collaboration of two Polish artists\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://soundcloud.com/mski\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/soundcloud.com/mski?referer=');\\">Piotr Matkowski</a>\\xC2\\xA0and\\xC2\\xA0<a href=\\"http://justanothervideo.tumblr.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/justanothervideo.tumblr.com/?referer=');\\">Jaga Slowinska</a>. \\xC2\\xA0They have an EP in the works, but have given all a visual intro via &#8220;COCO&#8221;, a beautifully stuttered electronic trip melded with a collage of video footage. \\xC2\\xA0Check out more via <a href=\\"http://www.thefader.com/2012/02/06/videos-hov-just-another-video-about-sunset-and-coco/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.thefader.com/2012/02/06/videos-hov-just-another-video-about-sunset-and-coco/?referer=');\\">The Fader </a>and <a href=\\"http://www.secretdecoder.net/2012/02/video-hov-coco.html\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.secretdecoder.net/2012/02/video-hov-coco.html?referer=');\\">Decoder</a>.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>    <iframe src=\\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/35954011\\" width=\\"500\\" height=\\"281\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\\n\\\n    <p>HOV Links: <a href=\\"http://hov-hov.org/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/hov-hov.org/?referer=');\\">Website</a></p>\\n\\\n    <img src=\\"http://pastaprima.net/?ak_action=api_record_view&id=12738&type=feed\\" alt=\\"\\" />"\n  entry_id: http://pastaprima.net/?p=12738\n  published: 2012-02-13 14:00:12 Z\n  summary: "HOV is the audio/visual collaboration of two Polish artists\\xC2\\xA0Piotr Matkowski\\xC2\\xA0and\\xC2\\xA0Jaga Slowinska. \\xC2\\xA0They have an EP in the works, but have given all a visual intro via &#8220;COCO&#8221;, a beautifully stuttered electronic trip melded with a collage of video footage. \\xC2\\xA0Check out more via The Fader and Decoder. HOV Links: Website"\n  title: "HOV \\xE2\\x80\\x93 COCO"\n  url: http://pastaprima.net/video/hov-coco/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: laurent the laurent\n  categories: \n  - Artist Reviews\n  - bittertv\n  content: "<p><img class=\\"alignnone size-full wp-image-12736\\" title=\\"bittertv loveritual EP\\" src=\\"http://pastaprima.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/loveritual-EP.jpg\\" alt=\\"bittertv loveritual EP\\" width=\\"496\\" height=\\"496\\" /></p>\\n\\\n    <p>The fine folks over at <a href=\\"http://flashlighttagmusic.tumblr.com/post/17267647928\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/flashlighttagmusic.tumblr.com/post/17267647928?referer=');\\">Flashlight Tag</a> turned me onto Russia&#8217;s bittertv. \\xC2\\xA0This is some chilled chillout electronics warped by the fading sun. \\xC2\\xA0These two tracks are from their <em>loveritual</em> EP which is available for free on <a href=\\"http://bittertv.bandcamp.com/\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/bittertv.bandcamp.com/?referer=');\\">Bandcamp</a>:</p>\\n\\\n    <p>mp3: <a title=\\"bittertv - firstloveritual\\" href=\\"http://fakepennycomics.com/blog/BT_firstloveritual.mp3\\" onclick=\\"pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/fakepennycomics.com/blog/BT_firstloveritual.mp3?referer=');\\">bittertv -\\xC2\\xA0firstloveritual</a></p>\\n\\\n