14	Eaten By Monsters	 Eaten by Monsters	--- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSS \ndescription: Music, comment, nonsense, and a bit more music...\nentries: \n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Tom\n  categories: \n  - EP\n  - music\n  - review\n  - Sticky Notes & Paper Scraps\n  - Town Hall\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2012/02/townhall.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1133\\" title=\\"TownHall\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2012/02/townhall.jpg?w=510&#038;h=363\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"510\\" height=\\"363\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>When a video of a band covering Jimmy Eat World&#8217;s <em><a href=\\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vR3oa2r5qtE&amp;feature=player_embedded\\">The Middle</a></em> landed in my inbox a month or so ago, the first thing that struck me was that it was really, really slick. \\xC2\\xA0It purported to be a &#8216;live&#8217; session, but the production values for both the sound and the visuals were far above what one normally expects from a hitherto unknown band (Brooklyn-based indie-folk outfit <a href=\\"http://www.facebook.com/TownHallBand\\">Town Hall </a>may have released their debut,\\xC2\\xA0<em>Tour EP</em>, at least a year ago, but I&#8217;d certainly never heard of them before). \\xC2\\xA0The impressive video &#8211; and it&#8217;s equally impressive collection of microphones and instruments &#8211; makes more sense upon learning that the\\xC2\\xA0<em>Tour EP</em> made its way into the hands of the prodigiously talented (or at the very least prodigiously dedicated) people at <a href=\\"http://www.masonjarmusic.com/\\">Mason Jar Music</a>.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>This self-styled collective of creative types specialize in both video work and sound production, with instrumental arrangement being their speciality. \\xC2\\xA0They&#8217;ve teamed up with Town Hall to re-record and re-release their EP, which is\\xC2\\xA0now called\\xC2\\xA0<em><a href=\\"http://townhall.bandcamp.com/\\">Sticky Notes &amp; Paper Scraps</a></em> and boasts the work of a deft and accomplished sonic touch. \\xC2\\xA0I&#8217;m often disparaging of bands using covers to help break themselves into the mainstream, but perhaps I ought to re-evaluate my stance; in this instance the cover served as an effective gateway drug into a band with a genuinely beautiful aesthetic and some cracking songs to match it.</p>\\n\\\n    <object data=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=1923123645/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\" type=\\"text/html\\" classid=\\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\\" width=\\"400\\" height=\\"100\\"><param name=\\"movie\\" value=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=1923123645/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\"><param name=\\"quality\\" value=\\"high\\" /><param name=\\"allowScriptAccess\\" value=\\"never\\" /><param name=\\"allowNetworking\\" value=\\"always\\" /><param name=\\"wmode\\" value=\\"transparent\\" /><object data=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=1923123645/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\" type=\\"text/html\\" width=\\"400\\" height=\\"100\\"></object></object>\\n\\\n    <object data=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=3959397477/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\" type=\\"text/html\\" classid=\\"clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000\\" width=\\"400\\" height=\\"100\\"><param name=\\"movie\\" value=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=3959397477/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\"><param name=\\"quality\\" value=\\"high\\" /><param name=\\"allowScriptAccess\\" value=\\"never\\" /><param name=\\"allowNetworking\\" value=\\"always\\" /><param name=\\"wmode\\" value=\\"transparent\\" /><object data=\\"http://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/track=3959397477/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/size=venti/\\" type=\\"text/html\\" width=\\"400\\" height=\\"100\\"></object></object>\\n\\\n    <br />  <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://f