box a month or so ago, the first thing that struck me was that it was really, really slick. \\xC2\\xA0It purported to be a &#8216;live&#8217; session, but the production values for both the sound and the visuals were far above [...]<img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com&amp;blog=5170812&amp;post=1132&amp;subd=eatenbymonsters&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\\" width=\\"1\\" height=\\"1\\" />"\n  title: "Sticky Notes & Paper Scraps: Town Hall"\n  url: http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/2012/02/18/sticky-notes-paper-scraps-town-hall/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Tom\n  categories: \n  - List\n  - music\n  - news\n  - Beth Jeans Haughton\n  - blogsound2012\n  - Daughter\n  - French Wives\n  - Friends\n  - Theme Park\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/theblogsound_final51.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1125\\" title=\\"TheBlogSound_final5\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/theblogsound_final51.jpg?w=510&#038;h=382\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"510\\" height=\\"382\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>As promised, here&#8217;s the shortlist for the Blog Sound of 2012. \\xC2\\xA0While the BBC&#8217;s poll, which inspired this alternative list, will be announced by a suspense-inducing day-by-day countdown, us humble bloggers are releasing our top five all in one go. \\xC2\\xA0In the interests of full disclosure, I should say now that none of these five acts were voted for by me, and I hadn&#8217;t even heard of Daughter or Theme Park before the longlist\\xC2\\xA0announcement. \\xC2\\xA0Nevertheless, I have been doing my homework on behalf of the blog &#8211; tirelessly and giving no quarter &#8211; and shall be reporting back soon with posts on all the best acts from the longlist. \\xC2\\xA0Until then, here&#8217;s the Blog Sound of 2012 shortlist:</p>\\n\\\n    <p><strong><a href=\\"http://ohdaughter.bandcamp.com/\\" tar