ram name=\\"movie\\" value=\\"http://player.soundcloud.com/player.swf?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F29258961&amp;g=1&amp;auto_play=false&amp;player_type=artwork&amp;color=ff0034\\"></param><embed height=\\"220\\" src=\\"http://player.soundcloud.com/player.swf?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F29258961&amp;g=1&amp;auto_play=false&amp;player_type=artwork&amp;color=ff0034\\" type=\\"application/x-shockwave-flash\\" width=\\"220\\"> </embed> </object></p>\\n\\\n    <p><strong><a href=\\"http://www.myspace.com/friends\\" target=\\"_blank\\">1.Friends</a></strong></p>\\n\\\n    <p><strong></strong><object height=\\"220\\" width=\\"220\\"><param name=\\"wmode\\" value=\\"transparent\\"><param name=\\"movie\\" value=\\"http://player.soundcloud.com/player.swf?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F23253035&amp;g=1&amp;auto_play=false&amp;player_type=artwork&amp;color=ff0034\\"></param><embed height=\\"220\\" src=\\"http://player.soundcloud.com/player.swf?url=http%3A%2F%2Fapi.soundcloud.com%2Ftracks%2F23253035&amp;g=1&amp;auto_play=false&amp;player_type=artwork&amp;color=ff0034\\" type=\\"application/x-shockwave-flash\\" width=\\"220\\"> </embed> </object></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Thanks go again to <a href=\\"http://vonpipmusicalexpress.wordpress.com/\\">Andy</a>, <a href=\\"http://www.breakingmorewaves.blogspot.com/\\">Robin</a>, and <a href=\\"http://sweepingthenation.blogspot.com/\\">Simon</a> for conceiving this alternative poll.</p>\\n\\\n    <br />  <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gofacebook/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/facebook/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gotwitter/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/twitter/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1123/\\" /></a> <img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com&amp;blog=5170812&amp;post=1123&amp;subd=eatenbymonsters&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\\" width=\\"1\\" height=\\"1\\" />"\n  entry_id: http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/?p=1123\n  published: 2012-01-02 09:00:03 Z\n  summary: "As promised, here&#8217;s the shortlist for the Blog Sound of 2012. \\xC2\\xA0While the BBC&#8217;s poll, which inspired this alternative list, will be announced by a suspense-inducing day-by-day countdown, us humble bloggers are releasing our top five all in one go. \\xC2\\xA0In the interests of full disclosure, I should say now that none of these five [...]<img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com&amp;blog=5170812&amp;post=1123&amp;subd=eatenbymonsters&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\\" width=\\"1\\" height=\\"1\\" />"\n  title: Blog Sound of 2012 Short List\n  url: http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/2012/01/02/blog-sound-of-2012-short-list/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Tom\n  categories: \n  - List\n  - music\n  - Yearly Top 10\n  - Admiral Fallow\n  - Bright Eyes. Emmy the Great\n  - Chris Thile\n  - Cold War Kids\n  - death cab for cutie\n  - FOUND\n  - Gotye\n  - Jon Hopkins\n  - Jonnie Common\n  - King Creosote\n  - Michael Daves\n  - Peter Gabriel\n  content: "<p><a href=\\"http://hypem.com/zeitgeist/2011/album-picker/derfus2\\"><img src=\\"http://hypem.com/zeitgeist/2011/widget/derfus2.png\\" alt=\\"\\" /></a><br />\\n\\\n    Geographically speaking, I don&#8217;t think I could be further from Scotland and still be in the UK. \\xC2\\xA0You&#8217;d never guess that from reading this blog however, as Scottish acts seem to be dominating my tastes for the last few years. \\xC2\\xA02011 has been no exception, and four albums on this list have their roots firmly planted north of the borders. \\xC2\\xA0As well as being a year for\\xC2\\xA0Scots, 2011 appears to be the year of the Return To Form. \\xC2\\xA0In itself this is a good thing, as recent years have seen more\\xC2\\xA0disappointing\\xC2\\xA0highly-hyped albums than good ones, but it means there&#8217;s a higher than normal percentage of &#8216;old pros&#8217; in this year&#8217;s list: amazingly, only one album on this list is a debut.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>At this point an\\xC2\\xA0honourable\\xC2\\xA0mention ought to go Chris Thile and Michael Daves\\xC2\\xA0for their album <em>Sleep With One Eye Open</em>. \\xC2\\xA0The Hype Machine&#8217;s widget for compiling their annual Zietgeist list didn&#8217;t recognize the Jonnie Common record, so albums 9 and 10 got bumped up a place, meaning Thile and Daves were promoted to the number ten spot on my Hype Machine list, but didn&#8217;t make the top ten proper.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>So without further ado, here is the moment you&#8217;ve all been waiting for since January; the official Eaten by Monsters blog Top Ten of 2010:</p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/making-mirrors.jpeg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1091\\" title=\\"making-mirrors\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/making-mirrors.jpeg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>10.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Making Mirrors</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Gotye.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0I umm-ed and ah-ed about whether this one would make the cut or not, as it isn&#8217;t a perfect record by any standards, and at times it strays far from what I would normally consider to be tasteful. \\xC2\\xA0For all it&#8217;s\\xC2\\xA0occasional\\xC2\\xA0flaws however, when it&#8217;s good it&#8217;s very, very good. \\xC2\\xA0His duet with Kimbra on<em>\\xC2\\xA0Somebody That I Used To Know</em> is a particular highlight, and the album is worth owning purely on the strength of that track alone.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FGotye_SomebodyThatIUsedToKnow.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/cover13.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1092\\" title=\\"mine is yours\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/cover13.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>9.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Mine Is Yours</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Cold War Kids.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0This one is simply fantastic right from the very first seconds. \\xC2\\xA0<em>Robbers and Coward</em>, from back in 2006 (and particularly the track <em>We Used To Vacation</em>), earned Cold War Kids a fairly\\xC2\\xA0unassailable\\xC2\\xA0position of prestige in casa EbM, but 2008&#8242;s <em>Loyalty to Loyalty</em>\\xC2\\xA0didn&#8217;t quite live up to expectation. \\xC2\\xA0As a result, the return to form displayed in <em>Mine Is Yours</em>\\xC2\\xA0is all the more satisfying.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FColdWarKids_MineIsYours.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/jonnie-common-master-of-none-lst086452.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1093\\" title=\\"jonnie-common-master-of-none-LST086452\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/jonnie-common-master-of-none-lst086452.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>8.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Master of None</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Jonnie Common.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0 Despite my taste for singer-songwriter-style songwriting with\\xC2\\xA0esoteric\\xC2\\xA0electronic noises, it seems to be a micro-genre that is very infrequently mastered. \\xC2\\xA0Many try and fail to marry the two almost-mutually-exclusive textures, so when it&#8217;s pulled off\\xC2\\xA0successfully I&#8217;m over the moon, and rarely will you hear it\\xC2\\xA0achieved\\xC2\\xA0with such aplomb and deftness of touch that&#8217;s displayed on <em>Master of None</em>.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FJonnieCommon_HandHand.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span><br />\\n\\\n    <a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/peoples-key.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1096\\" title=\\"peoples-key\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/peoples-key.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>7.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>The People&#8217;s Key</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Bright Eyes.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0Even more than Cold War Kids, the team behind Bright Eyes &#8211; Conor Oberst, Mike Mogis et al &#8211; have been slipping off their game of late. \\xC2\\xA0As much as their early efforts number among my favourite albums of all time, <em>Cassadaga</em>\\xC2\\xA0just doesn&#8217;t sit well with me. \\xC2\\xA0By all accounts <em>The People&#8217;s Key</em>\\xC2\\xA0will be the last album to bear the &#8216;Bright Eyes&#8217; label, and I&#8217;m sincerely relieved that they managed to get all cylinders firing for their swan song.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FBrightEyes_ShellGames.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/virtue.jpeg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1095\\" title=\\"virtue\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/virtue.jpeg?w=147&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"147\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>6.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Virtue</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Emmy the Great</strong>. \\xC2\\xA0The trouble with Emmy&#8217;s debut album,\\xC2\\xA0<em>First Love</em>, was that all the best songs had been floating around for ages before the album was conceived. \\xC2\\xA0What drew me to the early demos was the almost brutal juxtaposition of Emmy&#8217;s voice and her lyrical content, thrown into sharp relief by the decidedly amateurish nature of the recordings. \\xC2\\xA0The pristine album cuts, shorn of all their grit and viciousness, left the album itself sounding weak by comparison. \\xC2\\xA0With <em>Virtue</em>\\xC2\\xA0 &#8211; her second full-length &#8211; the production is even slicker, but this time it&#8217;s a blessing and not a curse.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FEmmyTheGreat_AWomanAWomanACenturyOfSleep.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/codes-and-keys-cover.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1097\\" title=\\"codes-and-keys-cover\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/codes-and-keys-cover.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>5.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Codes and Keys</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Death Cab For Cutie.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0The last of the returns-to-form in this list, and by now the story&#8217;s a familiar one: astounding early albums, a\\xC2\\xA0disappointing\\xC2\\xA0last record, and finally the triumph that we&#8217;ve been waiting for. \\xC2\\xA0<em>Codes and Keys</em>\\xC2\\xA0marks a return to the more studio-based recording approach that made the band&#8217;s best albums such complete joys to listen to and, surprise, surprise, it&#8217;s led to yet another fantastic album<em>.</em><span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FDeathCabForCutie_YouAreATourist.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/diamond-mine.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1098\\" title=\\"diamond mine\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/diamond-mine.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>4.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Diamond Mine</em>\\xC2\\xA0by King Creosote &amp; Jon Hopkins</strong>. \\xC2\\xA0The Mercury Prize nominations are always interesting from an academic viewpoint, but rarely &#8211; if ever &#8211; do they include an album that I&#8217;d include if I was compiling the list. \\xC2\\xA0Imagine my surprise, then, upon discovering that this year&#8217;s shortlist that included this KC gem. \\xC2\\xA0It&#8217;s not Kenny&#8217;s best record by a long way, but it&#8217;s testament to the strength of his other work that this sub-par effort nevertheless warrants a fourth place on this list.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FKingCreosote_BatsInTheAttic.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/admiral-fallow.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1099\\" title=\\"Admiral Fallow\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/admiral-fallow.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>3.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Boots Met My Face</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Admiral Fallow.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0I only discovered this album recently, having grown to love the track <em>Squealing Pigs</em>\\xC2\\xA0over a period of a few months, and it&#8217;s fast moved up the ranks of this year&#8217;s best albums. \\xC2\\xA0While technically this record had its first release last year, it was re-released back in March, so I&#8217;m claiming it as a 2011 record (if only because I&#8217;m ashamed to have missed it the first time around).<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FAdmiralFallow_SquealingPigs.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/peter-gabriel-new-blood.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1100\\" title=\\"Peter-Gabriel-New-Blood\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/peter-gabriel-new-blood.jpg?w=150&#038;h=150\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"150\\" /></a>2.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>New Blood</em>\\xC2\\xA0by Peter Gabriel.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0Last year&#8217;s <em>Scratch My Back</em>\\xC2\\xA0project saw Gabriel record orchestral covers of a host of popular songs, and while on paper that sounds like a heinous cringe-fest not fit for human consumption, it was actually rather impressive (although a few of the covers were as awful as the premise suggested, far more were haunting, effecting, moving and surprisingly powerful renditions). \\xC2\\xA0This year he gave the same treatment to his own back-catalogue and had even greater success. \\xC2\\xA0An assured and overwhelmingly impressive album, <em>New Blood</em>\\xC2\\xA0is a truly remarkable feat, especially coming from someone that I&#8217;d written off as having his best days long behind him.<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FPeterGabriel_TheRythmOfTheHeat.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/found_factorycraft.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-1101\\" title=\\"found_factorycraft\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/found_factorycraft.jpg?w=150&#038;h=147\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"150\\" height=\\"147\\" /></a>1.\\xC2\\xA0<strong><em>Factorycraft</em>\\xC2\\xA0by FOUND.</strong>\\xC2\\xA0For a long time now I&#8217;ve liked the <em>idea</em> of FOUND much more than I&#8217;ve liked their actual music. \\xC2\\xA0Heralded by reviewers far more familiar with the band than I as their most accessible record to date, they&#8217;re not wrong as I finally find myself loving FOUND&#8217;s music. \\xC2\\xA0Maybe my taste is more predictable and mainstream than I&#8217;d like to admit, but the only thing that really matters is that this is a simply super record.\\xC2\\xA0<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2F2011Top10%2FFound_YoureNoVincentGallo.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <br />  <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gofacebook/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/facebook/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gotwitter/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/twitter/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\"><img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/1090/\\" /></a> <img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com&amp;blog=5170812&amp;post=1090&amp;subd=eatenbymonsters&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\\" width=\\"1\\" height=\\"1\\" />"\n  entry_id: http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/?p=1090\n  published: 2011-12-31 00:58:00 Z\n  summary: "Geographically speaking, I don&#8217;t think I could be further from Scotland and still be in the UK. \\xC2\\xA0You&#8217;d never guess that from reading this blog however, as Scottish acts seem to be dominating my tastes for the last few years. \\xC2\\xA02011 has been no exception, and four albums on this list have their roots firmly [...]<img alt=\\"\\" border=\\"0\\" src=\\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com&amp;blog=5170812&amp;post=1090&amp;subd=eatenbymonsters&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\\" width=\\"1\\" height=\\"1\\" />"\n  title: Top 10 Albums of 2011\n  url: http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/2011/12/31/top-10-albums-of-2011/\n- !ruby/object:Feedzirra::Parser::RSSEntry \n  author: Tom\n  categories: \n  - music\n  - christmas\n  - The Very Foundation\n  content: "<p><em>[There's plenty of great Christmas songs out there, but most suffer terribly from over-exposure. \\xC2\\xA0To remedy that, EbM presents a selection of <a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.wordpress.com/category/alternative-christmas/\\">alternative Christmas songs</a>.]</em></p>\\n\\\n    <p><a href=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/theveryfoundation.jpg\\"><img class=\\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1087\\" title=\\"theveryfoundation\\" src=\\"http://eatenbymonsters.files.wordpress.com/2011/12/theveryfoundation.jpg?w=510&#038;h=408\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"510\\" height=\\"408\\" /></a></p>\\n\\\n    <p>Well we&#8217;ve finally made it to the end, and it turns out these little single-song showcase posts have been quite popular; I&#8217;ll have to do it again sometime. \\xC2\\xA0Since Christmas is practically upon us now, I thought I&#8217;d better post what I consider to be the best Christmas song ever. \\xC2\\xA0In fact, this little number from <a href=\\"http://theveryfoundation.com/\\">The Very Foundation</a>\\xC2\\xA0(courtesy of <a href=\\"http://www.xopublicity.com/xofortheholidays4.html\\">XO for the Holidays</a> 2009 comp.) is a song that ought to be an all-time-top-song of mine, but it&#8217;s just so Christmasy that to listen to it outside of December would just feel wrong. \\xC2\\xA0As it is, I savour the short time that I can get away with playing it on almost constant repeat. \\xC2\\xA0Witty and at times ridiculous, yet always displaying a proper Christmas spirit (without ever descending into schmaltz), this is, in my view, the very best that Christmas music has to offer.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>I hope all your day&#8217;s are merry and bright, and merry Christmas to all, and to all a good night.</p>\\n\\\n    <p>The Very Foundation &#8211; <a href=\\"http://www.bearfacedrecords.com/EbMBlog_mp3s/Christmas/TheVeryFoundation_AllLitUp.mp3\\">All Lit Up (For Christmas)</a>\\xC2\\xA0<span style='text-align:left;display:block;'><p><object type='application/x-shockwave-flash' data='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' width='290' height='24' id='audioplayer1'><param name='movie' value='http://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/audio-player/player.swf' /><param name='FlashVars' value='&amp;bg=0xf8f8f8&amp;leftbg=0xeeeeee&amp;lefticon=0x666666&amp;rightbg=0xcccccc&amp;rightbghover=0x999999&amp;righticon=0x666666&amp;righticonhover=0xffffff&amp;text=0x666666&amp;slider=0x666666&amp;track=0xFFFFFF&amp;border=0x666666&amp;loader=0x9FFFB8&amp;soundFile=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bearfacedrecords.com%2FEbMBlog_mp3s%2FChristmas%2FTheVeryFoundation_AllLitUp.mp3' /><param name='quality' value='high' /><param name='menu' value='false' /><param name='bgcolor' value='#FFFFFF' /><param name='wmode' value='opaque' /></object></p></span></p>\\n\\\n    <br />  <a rel=\\"nofollow\\" href=\\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/eatenbymonsters.wordpres