65	the interview show: Grimes	Scott Wood	http://winniecooper.net/2012/02/the-interview-show-grimes/	<p>We&#8217;re BACK! (Don&#8217;t call it a comeback. We&#8217;ve been here for years.)</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter" src="http://www.winniecooper.net/scott/february 2012/grimes.jpg" alt="" width="460" height="298" /></p>\n<p><strong>Grimes</strong> is a musician, visual artist, video director and producer based out of Montreal/Vancouver and lately <span style="text-decoration: underline">everyone</span> has been falling under her spell.</p>\n<p>Influential UK music mag <a href="http://www.nme.com/blog/index.php?blog=147&amp;p=11697&amp;title=top_20_new_bands_of_2012_the_big_picture&amp;more=1&amp;c=1">NME picked her as one of the most exciting acts of 2012</a>. Listen to her latest record <em><strong>Visions</strong></em> and you would have to agree.</p>\n<p>When I sat down with <strong>Grimes</strong>, she was a lot more giggly than I would have expected, but she had a lot to say when I asked her about &#8220;not knowing any music theory&#8221; (a controversial rumor about her) and her <em><strong></strong></em>witch house roots.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.winniecooper.net/scott/february 2012/tis Grimes.mp3"><strong>the interview show</strong> with <strong>Grimes</strong></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.winniecooper.net/scott/february 2012/Oblivion.mp3">Grimes &#8220;Oblivion&#8221;</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.winniecooper.net/scott/february 2012/Grimes - Crystal Ball (Nautiluss Remix).mp3">Grimes &#8220;Crystal Ball&#8221; (Nautiluss Remix)</a></p>\n<p>Thanks for listening. We are back with an all-new series of new episodes. Stay tuned for my chats with <strong>Philoceraptor</strong>, <strong>K.Flay</strong>, <strong>The Wombats</strong>, <strong>Myths</strong>, <strong>TheeSatisfaction</strong>, <strong>Paper Lions</strong>, <strong>Metronomy</strong>, <strong>Braids</strong> and many many more.</p>\n<p><strong>Grimes</strong> just kicked off a <a href="http://http://4ad.com/artists/grimes/live">big tour with North American and European dates</a>. Check her out if she comes your way.</p>\n<div><strong>Posted by <a href="http://twitter.com/interview_show"><a href="http://twitter.com/interview_show">@interview_show</a></a>.</strong></div>\n<div>\n<h6><strong><em><a title="Posts tagged with the interview show" href="..-interview-show/" rel="tag">the interview show</a></em></strong> is everywhere! (interviewshow[at]gmail.com)<br />\nfollow us on twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/interview_show"><a href="http://twitter.com/interview_show">@interview_show</a></a></h6>\n<h6><strong><a href="http://www.cjsf.ca/" target="_blank">www.cjsf.ca</a></strong> (Vancouver, BC, Mondays 4:30-5pm PST and Wednesdays 12:30am PST)<a href="http://www.ckdu.ca/" target="_blank"><strong><br />\nwww.ckdu.ca</strong></a> (Halifax, NS, Saturdays 1:30-2:00am AST)<br />\n<strong><a href="http://www.radiocfxu.ca/" target="_blank">www.radiocfxu.ca</a></strong> (Campus Community Radio, Antigonish, NS, Fridays 11pm-12am AST)<br />\n<strong><a href="http://www.cfru.ca/" target="_blank">www.cfru.ca</a></strong> (University of Guelph Radio, ON, Tuesdays 3pm EST)<br />\n<strong><a href="http://www.umfm.com/" target="_blank">www.umfm.com</a></strong> (Winnipeg’s Hit Free Radio, MB, Fridays 6-6:30pm CST)<br />\n<strong><a href="http://www.caperradio.com/" target="_blank">www.caperradio.com</a></strong> (Cape Breton University Radio, NS, Wednesdays 2:30-3pm AST and Fridays 5:30-6pm AST)<br />\nPermalink: <a href="http://www.winniecooper.net/tag/the-interview-show/">www.winniecooper.net/tag/the-interview-show/</a></h6>\n</div>\n\n\t\t\t\t<!-- Social Sharing Toolkit v2.0.4 | http://www.marijnrongen.com/wordpress-plugins/social_sharing_toolkit/ -->\n\t\t\t\t<div class="mr_social_sharing_wrapper"><span class="mr_social_sharing"><iframe src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/like.php?locale=en_US&amp;href=http%3A%2F%2Fwinniecooper.net%2F2012%2F02%2Fthe-interview-